    ],
    "claim": "Native funding is validated per swap leg instead of cumulatively. `depositAsset` only checks `msg.value >= amount` for the current leg, while `depositAssets` loops over all `requiresDeposit` swaps and reuses the same `msg.value` each time. Multiple native legs can therefore collectively spend more ETH than the caller supplied, and later `call{value:nativeValue}` executions draw the shortfall from the contract's existing ETH balance.",
    "impact": "If the contract holds ETH, an attacker can amplify a single payment across many native-input swaps and convert or withdraw the contract's ETH to themselves.",
